May be a stupid remark, but for me, a symmetric competition would mean 
\begin_inset Formula $\alpha_{ij}=\alpha_{ji}$
\end_inset

, not necessarily 
\begin_inset Formula $\alpha_{ij}=\alpha_{ii}$
\end_inset


